tr: learning and coming to understand ideas and information
example: his appetite for facts was better than his digestion

tr: the organic process by which food is converted into substances that can be absorbed into the body
the process of decomposing organic matter (as in sewage) by bacteria or by chemical action or heat

value.def: Digestion is the process of digesting food.

example.ex: No liquids are served with meals because they interfere with digestion.
example.tran: 上饭菜时不要同时上汤水或饮品，因为这会影响消化。

value.def: Your digestion is the system in your body which digests your food.

example.ex: My digestion ain't so hot these days, either.
example.tran: 我的消化系统这几天也不怎么对劲儿。

trans: 酸消化法；酸消解；酸分解

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to carry, to bring 带来
rootsaffixes.title: gest, gister

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 加强 + gest 带来 → 带来很多 → 充满
di 分开 + gest 带来 → 带下去 → 消化
gest 带来 + iculate 表动作 → 做手势
gest 带来 + ure 表行为 → 能带来信息的动作 → 手势
in 不 + digestion 消化 → 消化不良
re 重新 + gister 带来 → 再次带来〔新来的学生〕→〔学员〕登记，注册
sug 下 + gest 带来 → 从下面带上来〔话〕→ 建议
